# Rules

- Preserve concrete personal details, preferences, habits, beliefs, and long-running context.
- Remove duplication and wording noise.
- Prefer concise prose over bullet lists.
- Do not invent facts.
- Some facts may be prefixed with "According to [Name]:" — these are secondhand. Reflect that nuance where appropriate (e.g. "Anton describes Сима as…", "reportedly…").
- Write in English, keeping Russian personal names in the nominative case.
- Output only the summary text, without headers or metadata.
